# Curio — Visualisation Grammar Integration Refactor

> **Contribution by Simran Mishra & Yukta Salvi · 2026**
> Forked from [urban-toolkit/curio](https://github.com/urban-toolkit/curio)

---

## What This Fork Does

This fork refactors Curio's visualisation grammar execution into a **shared, extensible, adapter-based pipeline**. Instead of each grammar (Vega-Lite, UTK) owning a bespoke lifecycle hook, all grammars now flow through a single `GrammarExecutionLayer` that selects the right adapter at runtime.

The changes reduce maintenance cost, improve consistency across grammars, and make adding future grammars a matter of writing one adapter — not a whole new lifecycle.

---

## Problem: The Old Architecture

Before this refactor, every grammar had its own isolated lifecycle hook:

```
[ Node ]
    └── [ UniversalBox ]
            └── [ Descriptor ] (getNodeDescriptor(nodeType))
                    ├── useVegaLifecycle  →  useVega  →  [Visualization]
                    └── useUtkLifecycle   →  useUtk   →  [Visualization]
```

**Pain points:**

- `useUTK` performed heavy preprocessing on every render: GeoJSON conversion, camera positioning, DOM setup, and custom `GrammarInterpreter` calls.
- Adding a new grammar meant writing a new lifecycle entirely from scratch.
- High maintenance surface — a bug in shared logic required fixes across multiple files.
- No shared validation layer meant inconsistent error messages between grammars.

---

## Solution: Adapter-Based Pipeline

The new architecture routes all grammars through a unified `GrammarExecutionLayer`:

```
[ Node ]
    └── [ UniversalBox ]
            └── [ Descriptor ] (getNodeDescriptor(nodeType))
                    └── useGrammarLifecycle
                            └── GrammarExecutionLayer.execute(IR)
                                    └── Adapter.render()
                                            └── [Visualization]
```

### Key Components

| Component | Role |
|---|---|
| `useGrammarLifecycle` | Single shared lifecycle hook used by all grammar node types |
| `GrammarExecutionLayer` | Receives an Intermediate Representation (IR) and dispatches to the correct adapter |
| `GrammarAdapterRegistry` | Maps grammar identifiers (e.g. `vega-lite`, `utk`, `d3`) to their adapter implementations |
| `Adapter.render()` | Grammar-specific rendering logic, cleanly isolated per grammar |

---

## Changes at a Glance

### Structural (Old → New)

| Before | After |
|---|---|
| `useVegaLifecycle` + `useUtkLifecycle` (separate) | `useGrammarLifecycle` (unified) |
| Custom preprocessing in each lifecycle | Preprocessing moved into each grammar's adapter |
| No shared validation | Shared Grammar Validation Layer |
| New grammar = new lifecycle file | New grammar = new adapter registration |

### Shared Grammar Validation Layer

A new validation layer was added before execution to provide consistent error feedback across grammars. Findings from testing:

| Scenario | Vega-Lite (before) | UTK (before) | After |
|---|---|---|---|
| Empty grammar `{}` | Clear invalid spec popup | Blank output, no message | Consistent error state |
| Invalid JSON | Detailed parse error | Generic error only | Unified parse error |
| Wrong data type (DataFrame vs GeoDataFrame) | Works | Rejects silently | Clear type-mismatch message |

