## Extensibility Proof: D3.js Grammar

To prove the architecture works for any grammar, a mock D3 grammar (`VIS_D3`) was implemented end-to-end without touching any existing lifecycle code:

| Step | What Happened |
|---|---|
| 1 | Defined a `VIS_D3` node type following the same pattern as `vega-lite` and `utk` |
| 2 | Wrote a descriptor mapping `d3` → `useGrammarLifecycle` (no custom lifecycle needed) |
| 3 | Registered a `d3` adapter in the `GrammarAdapterRegistry` |
| 4 | Called `executeVisualization` — correct adapter selected automatically |
| 5 | Real DOM output rendered with no manual lifecycle invocation |

This confirms that adding future grammars (e.g. Observable Plot, Deck.gl) requires only steps 2–3 above.

